<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 05 at 1:31AM CDT  by NWS Lubbock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Motley and
southeastern Hall Counties through 200 AM CDT...
At 131 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Flomot, or 12 miles south of Turkey, moving east at 40
mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Northfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
